New vehicle assessment programmes
In these days of storms and accidents, not only deserve the CFZ workshops
Every day, thousands of vehicles engaged in an accident are dragged into the workshops where an expert has to assess the damages caused and the cost of repair.
No accident is equal and the calculation of the costs of parts and hours of work can be a long and complicated task.
The calculation of repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros by hand, including parts and working hours, may take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the help of the latest computer tools, it is a question of minutes
Therefore, nearly 100 % of experts use this type of system.
The service and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs collect the information they receive from the manufacturers to process them afterwards and offer them to their customers in the form of a useful programme.
In Spain Audatex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all opinions are produced with their products.
The two other companies competing with the tool market for review and drafting a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data that the manufacturers provide is nothing but simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, sales manager of Audatex, it is cooperated with 63 manufacturers and importers, each of which provides the information in a different format.
Moreover, the data to be processed is becoming increasingly larger, until the point that in the last five years more versions, variants and motorizations have been placed on the market than in the past fifteen years.
As soon as a new car comes to the market, the work begins for the companies.
It is a difficult task, because each individual of the Butthousand car parts must be catagolized and its price entered.
In addition, each model creates a "intelligent" graphic image on which you can "click" different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a much sold model, work can be completed in a week if the procedure is progressing rapidly.
If this is a less common car, it can last up to three or four months. Currently Audatex has 99.2% of cars distributed in Spain with complete information.
Among the more exclusive models, they have information about the Porsche models, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the road-driving vehicle park, there are more than 99%.
For the purpose of carrying out the documentation and the production of databases, Audatex has eight worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them has specialized in certain brands.
The national headquarters are located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually professionals for mechanics) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests EUR 90 million annually in the preparation of these databases.
Every month they record 2.5 million data and their customers get the updates every second day.
